               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 1ra-101ra) 
 I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 1ra-8ra) 
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book (fols. 1ra-4rb)
 - Story of the family of Adam (fols.
                     4rb-8ra)
 I-2) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: 49 miracles (fols.
                     8ra-98vb)
 I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd la-malakotǝka... “I worship Thy Godhead…”
                     (99ra-101ra)
 
 Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Most miracles are numbered (the number 1 is missing before the first
                        miracle; instead of number 5, the number 14 is written). Miracles are
                        introduced with the words mǝʕraf ‘chapter’, zǝkr ‘memory’, täʔammǝr
                        ‘miracles’, nägär ‘speech’</note>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus from="103rb" to="103va">103rb-103va</locus>: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአጽሐፍክዋ፡ ቄስ፡ ወልደ፡
                        ጊዮርጊስ፡ በወርቅሃ፡ ከመ፡ ትኩነኒ፡ መርሐ፡ ውስተ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ኢትርስኡኒ፡ በጊዜ፡ ጸሎት። ወዕጣን። ወበጊዜ፡
                        ቍርባን። ፩አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡ በሞትየ፡ ወበሕይወትየ። ኢትርስዑኒ፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ውጉዘ፡
                        ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን። The colophon mentions qes Walda Giyorgis
                        Bäwärqǝha, the commissioner of the manuscript. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
